<%# locals: (current_workspace:, sidebar_partial:) -%>
<%# Desktop settings-sidebar wrapper — provides the <aside> landmark
    and the boxed sidebar visual chrome (fixed 256px width, surface
    background, right border). The actual contents (nav items + Pundit
    gating) are provided by the caller via sidebar_partial:, which resolves
    to either _identity_settings_sidebar_items or
    _workspace_settings_sidebar_items depending on which context the
    controller declared via settings_context :identity/:workspace.

    Below md, the same items source instead renders as an in-page
    section-nav strip (see _section_nav_strip) — not this <aside>.
    Workspace switching is handled by the header switcher
    (#workspace-switcher-button) added in Phase 2b. -%>
<aside aria-label="<%= t("settings.sidebar.aria_label") %>"
       class="w-64 shrink-0 px-4 py-6 border-r border-border bg-surface">
  <%= render sidebar_partial,
        current_workspace: current_workspace %>
</aside>
